ndering why the other person is so unfair/wrong, or one can just accept it =
as the fruits given by the Lord for one's previous actions and focus the mi=
nd on what good actions can be performed *now*. Similarly, when people prai=
se one, one has a choice. One can either become excited and gloat in the pr=
aises or one can think that the Lord used one as an instrument in getting t=
